###TASK -2 

To write a pod file and to then host it on k8s
first to create a yaml file:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  creationTimestamp: null
  labels:
    adhoc: kitkat
  name: adhocpod1
spec:
  containers:
  - image: nginx
    name: adhocpod1
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    resources: {}
  dnsPolicy: ClusterFirst
  restartPolicy: Never
status: {}
   
once created, use,
   $ kubectl create â€“f q2.yml
   
 for  kitkat.yml:
```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: kitkat
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    adhoc: kitkat
  ports:
    - port: 80
      targetPort: 80
```
command:
kubectl create -f kitkat.yml

